### SP 800-171 Revision 3 Requirement 3.1.8 (Unsuccessful Logon Attempts)
When the maximum number of unsuccessful attempts is exceeded, the system must automatically perform one or more of the following selected actions [3]:
* Lock the account or node for an organization-defined time period [3];
* Lock the account or node until released by an administrator [3];
* Delay the next logon prompt [3];
* Notify the system administrator [3]; or
* Take other action [3].

### SP 800-171 Revision 3 Requirement 3.2.1 (Literacy Training and Awareness)
Organizations must provide security literacy training to system users [11]:
* As part of initial training for new users and at an organization-defined frequency thereafter [11];
* When required by system changes or following organization-defined events [11]; and
* On recognizing and reporting indicators of insider threat, social engineering, and social mining [11].
